processes.name: ECR Repo
processes.description:
AWS ECR (Elastic Container Registry ) plugin is used to create a repository.
Amazon Elastic Container Registry (ECR) is a fully managed container registry that makes it easy to store, manage, share, and deploy your container images and artifacts.

processes.name: Git Clone
processes.description: Git Clone method will download the source code from github repository.
AWS CodeBuild plugin  is a fully managed continuous integration service that compiles source code, runs tests, and produces software packages that are ready to deploy.
This AWS Code-pipeline plugin will help to create the AWS CI/CD Code-pipeline from JSON file.

processes.name: ECS Cluster
processes.description:
AWS ECS plugin is used to create the cluster to deploy the microservices.
Amazon ECS is a fully managed container orchestration service that makes it easy  to deploy, manage, and scale containerized applications.

processes.name: ECS Task
processes.description: This AWS-ECS Plugin method will define a  task definition which is required to run Docker containers in Amazon ECS.

processes.name: ECS Service
processes.description: This  Amazon ECS plugin will create a service which  allows you to run and maintain a specified number of instances of a task definition simultaneously in an Amazon ECS cluster.
